thomas o ryder  wikipedia thomas o ryder from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search thomas o ryder born  south carolina us residence connecticut nationality american alma mater louisiana state university occupation board member  director at amazoncom thomas o ryder born c  is an american businessman investor and corporate board member who has had a long career in the publishing and financial services industries he currently serves on the boards of directors of amazoncom interval leisure group inc quad graphics inc rpx corp inc and starwood hotels  resorts worldwide  contents  education and early career  american express  readers digest association  boards and chairmanships  former boards  awards  references education and early careeredit ryder was born in varnville sc but was raised in alexandria la where he attended public schools ryder received a bachelor of arts degree in journalism from louisiana state university in  after graduating from louisiana state university in  he was hired as a publishing trainee at time inc and in  became a publishing executive at xerox education publications in  he joined vincent drucker and frank mcculloch as the founding executive team in education today co inc in palo alto ca the company published magazines and books for teachers and parents including learning the magazine for creative teaching ryder was president of the company and a member of the board of directors from  until may  ryder was senior vice president of cbs magazines american expressedit ryder served as the president of american express travel related services international a division of american express company from october  to april  he had been president of american express merchantrelated services world wide and had joined the company as president of american express publishing world wide in may  readers digest associationedit ryder served as the chairman and chief executive officer at the readers digest association inc from april  to december  and served as its chairman of the board from april  to march  ryder retired from rda when the company was sold to a private equity firm  the readers digest association inc rda a global media and direct marketing company is best known for its flagship publication founded in  readers digest the company was founded by husband and wife dewitt and lila bell wallace in  with the first publication of readers digest magazine but grew to include a diverse range of magazines books music dvds and online content as chairman and ceo of the company that published the worlds most widely read magazine readers digest ryder was responsible for a total global circulation of almost  million and well over  million readers in  countries with company sales of nearly  billion  in  the company purchased reiman publications based in greendale wisconsin from madison dearborn partners reiman publications published taste of home healthy cooking simple and delicious birds  blooms country country woman farm and ranch living and reminisce it was one of the largest magazine publishing acquisitions in us history in march  after being publicly traded for  years readers digest association was acquired by an investor group led by ripplewood holdings a private equity firm on september   it was announced that the companys name was officially changed from readers digest association to trusted media brands inc  boards and chairmanshipsedit ryder has been an independent director at starwood hotels  resorts worldwide inc since april  he currently serves on the capital and compensation committees he formerly served on the governance committee and was chairman of the audit committee  since  ryder has served on the board of director of amazon nasdaq was named lead independent director and serves as the chairman of audit he serves on rpx corp since  pre ipo nyse and is the company’s lead independent director and is the former audit chairman he is currently on the compensation committee and is nominating chairman he has been on the board of quad graphics nyse since  and is on the audit committee former boardsedit ryder served as the chief executive officer of the readers digest association inc from april  to december  and served as its chairman of the board from april  to march  when the company was sold to a private equity firm he served on virgin mobile usa nyse from  and was chairman of the board audit committee chairman and a member of the compensation committee the company was acquired by sprintnextel in july  ryder served on world color press private from  and was lead independent director and a member of the audit committee the company was acquired by quad graphics in july  he served on startek corporationnyse from  –  and was chairman of the audit committee from  he swerved on the board of education today company inc private where he was ceo and cofounder he served on the boards of directors for club mediterranee and american express international bank awardsedit ryder was chairman of the board of the mpathe association of magazine media and was given the henry johnson fisher award in  for lifetime achievement in magazine publishing  ryder received an honorary doctor of humane letters from the university of southern connecticut on may   ryder was inducted into the lsu alumni hall of fame in   and in  the lsu manship school of mass communication hall of fame  referencesedit  leadership team starwoodcom retrieved april     thomas o ryder finewinemagazinecom retrieved april     httpswwwwsjcomarticlessb  httpwwwmagazineorgasmeaboutasmepressroomasmepressreleasesthomasoryderandlewislaphamreceivemagazineindustrylifetimeachievementawards  inc trusted media brands in historic move the readers digest association inc changes name to trusted media brands inc wwwprnewswirecom retrieved    httpwwwstarwoodhotelscomcorporateaboutleadershipryderhtmllanguageenus  httpwwwmagazineorgasmeaboutasmepressroomasmepressreleasesthomasoryderandlewislaphamreceivemagazineindustrylifetimeachiev